 This is part 3 of a series looking at World War II flying aces. In part 1, I showed how to download data from an a Wikipedia (html) table. Then in part 2 I showed some wrangling with dplyr and janitor, and some exploratory data analysis with inspectdf. We discovered that Germany had the highest average number of aerial victories.
